The paper deals with the problem of generating correlated random variables in a distributed fashion, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of common randomness and communication constraints also suggests a systems and control perspective (cs.SY) and a distributed computing aspect (cs.DC). Finally, the problem of generating correlated random variables has applications in networked systems (cs.NI).
